Senior Fraud Data Scientist
Date: 20-Jul-2022
Location: Sydney (Macquarie Park HQ), Australia
Company: Singtel Group
Your mission ...

As a Senior Data Scientist within our Group Credit Risk (GCR) function, you will develop and deploy capabilities that align to the business outcomes of higher sales, lower losses and increase automation and efficiency of the existing business model. The foundation of your expertise will be your ability to directly affect business results and meet GCR KPI’s by applying your analytical and technical skills in innovative ways.
You will use your understanding of business objectives and knowledge of the Credit portfolio to identify risks and opportunities – applying your technical expertise to extract, analyse and present the data required to support your recommendations!

Working with stakeholders across the Optus group, you will take a lead role in developing and delivering real time decisioning models that improve business outcomes across Fraud, Credit Risk and collections. A background in a Credit, Fraud or Collections environment is highly desirable and you will have proven experience with analytical problem solving.
Your key ingredients for success ...
Significant experience in a Senior Data Science role to date applying complex machine learning algorithms to solve business problems;
Experience with IT systems and decisioning platforms;
Credit management/Fraud risk management experience including risk scorecard modelling;
Experience in device intelligence fraud tools and customer ID authentication processes;
Advanced data analysis skills and knowledge of SQL programming, with experience in developing machine learning models across different topics such as predictive, pattern recognition, NLP and segmentation using large volumes of data through different machine learning algorithms;
Experience implementing machine learning algorithms such as decision trees, gradient boosting models, logistic regression, neural networks, etc; &
Proficient in the use Data-mining software and programming languages (SAS, R, Python), plus experience with Tableau, plus advanced MS Office.
If this sounds like you, please apply in confidence via the online function today!

As a provider of essential services across Australia, Optus has a critical role in the community through keeping our customers connected to the people they love and the things that matter. It is also our priority to ensure we provide our amazing people and our customers with a healthy and safe workplace environment. In light of the significant risks posed by COVID-19, Optus expects all workers to be fully vaccinated against COVID-19, and will require vaccination for certain roles as well as access to Optus workplaces. Please speak to us if you have any questions about this policy or how it impacts you, including any concerns you might have about meeting this requirement.

Optus is a place where we let you do you. We're a highly collaborative workplace, and offer a range of perks such as:
A competitive salary;
Discounts on products and services;
Ongoing training, mentoring and development opportunities;
Up to five days of Volunteer Leave per year; &
Blended Ways of Working

We understand that flexibility means different things to different people. We're proud to offer a variety of options to work in different ways, such as our Blended Ways of Working and job share. Our Blended Ways of Working lets our people work across home and our offices. Please talk to us about how we can make this role work for you.
Curious about our culture? Go behind the scenes with our people by searching #OptusLife on LinkedIn.
Please no recruitment agencies, we’ll be managing this role in-house. Any resumes submitted outside of our process will be deemed the sole property of Optus.

